<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A rectangular playground has length <m>(x + {4})</m> metres and width <m>x</m> metres. The width is increased by <m>{4}</m> metres.
</p>
<p>
Form and simplify an expression for the new area of the playground.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Original length = <m>x + {4}</m>
</p>

<p>
Original width = <m>x</m>
</p>

<p>
After the increase, the new width is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x + {4}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Area = length × width
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {4})(x + {4})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Multiply each term in the first bracket by each term in the second bracket:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x(x + {4}) + {4}(x + {4})
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= x^2 + {4}x + {4}x + {16}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Combine like terms:
</p>

<p>
<me>
= x^2 + {8}x + {16}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the new area in simplest form is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {8}x + {16}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+8 x+16</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>